I could understand if I was refusing to pay or leaving them hanging but I communicated the whole time and I was trying to pay them. I always caught them up if I ever was late  and always paid, I never didn't pay. When they confiscated all of my belongings I guess they decided that the value of my items was worth more than my business or loyalty.

text:
I drove 4 hours to visit this place after speaking with the representative thru email about reserving a spot.
(Which would be a MUCH longer drive with us bringing 2 trailers, might I add.) So we, loaded up one day and just drove down to check things out. After my round trip of 8 hours this week I emailed them to reserve several tables only to be told "they didn't have space to accommodate me" LOL (here's the answer to you folks complaining about no vendors)

I "HAD" planned on coming down with an assortment of new and used items in a 12 ft. enclosed trailer, 2 trucks loaded with what I could carry, and boxes of items loaded in my camper that is self contained of which I planned to stay in while there (I even spoke with multiple vendors that verified other sellers do this!) since it is such a long drive and I have two toddlers to also contend with it is the easiest option for me and no campgrounds (that I could locate) anywhere nearby that would be suitable for 2 trucks and 2 trailers.

So folks all I can say is have fun with whatever you can find down there! But, me personally, I will go buy and sell elsewhere. There's plenty of choices and management that understand how putting the safty of your family while selling items is a top priority.
